Read about
What is a Static Website?

Static websites are comprised of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript files that are pre-built and served to the user as-is, without any server-side processing. Unlike dynamic websites, static websites do not rely on databases or server-side scripting languages. Static web developers are responsible for creating and maintaining these websites.

Responsibilities of a Static Web Developer

a. Website Design: Static web developers collaborate with designers to transform visual mockups into functional websites. They ensure that the design is faithfully implemented and optimized for performance across different devices and browsers. b. HTML/CSS Development: Proficiency in HTML and CSS is essential for static web developers. They write clean, semantic code to structure the website's content and apply styles, ensuring a consistent and visually appealing user experience. c. JavaScript Integration: Static websites often require JavaScript for interactivity and enhanced functionality. Static web developers incorporate JavaScript libraries and frameworks to bring dynamic elements to the static site.

What is prossive website

Progressive web apps (PWAs) are a new way of developing web applications that combine the best of both worlds: the web and native apps. PWAs are web applications that can be accessed through a browser, but they also have the ability to be installed on the device, work offline, and integrate with the devices hardware and software
